It references / adapts ideas and interfaces from the following projects, each
under its own license:

- DeepSeek-V4 / DeepSeek-V4-Flash-DSpark checkpoint and reference inference code
  (deepseek-ai, MIT). https://huggingface.co/deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-DSpark
  - The DSpark draft-head architecture (DSparkBlock / markov_head / confidence_head)
    and weight layout (mtp.* namespace) are derived from the published reference
    inference/model.py and config.json.

- DeepSpec (deepseek-ai, MIT). https://github.com/deepseek-ai/DeepSpec
  - Model-agnostic DSpark algorithm (Markov bias, confidence / adaptive depth,
    accept/verify loop) referenced for the proposer logic.
  - DeepSpec itself includes code adapted from SpecForge (Apache-2.0) and the
    DFlash recipe (MIT); see DeepSpec's NOTICE.

- vLLM (vllm-project, Apache-2.0). https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm
  - The DSpark integration is implemented as vLLM patches (new speculative method
    `dspark`, a DeepSeek-V4 draft-head model class, and a DFlash-derived proposer).
  - SM12x (sm_120/sm_121) DeepSeek-V4 enablement builds on the jasl/vllm community fork.

No model weights are redistributed by this repository.
